==Italian, Spanish, Portuguese, Romanian, English, German, Ancient Roman, Roman Mythology ==
===Etymology===
Feminine form of [[Silvius]]

Derived from the [[Latin]] word "silva" meaning [[forest]]

===Usage===
In Myths, Rhea Silvia was the mother of famous twins [[Romulus]] and [[Remus]], the founders of [[Rome]]. 

6th-century saint Silvia was the mother of the [[pope]] [[Gregory the Great]].
